    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Timothy",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 5,
        "summary": "Saints are to care for their worthy poor\u2014Policies concerning elders are given.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Rebuke not an elder, but entreat him as a father; and the younger men as brethren;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Respect.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, with all purity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Honour widows that are widows indeed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Widows.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But if any widow have children or nephews, let them learn first to shew piety at home, and to requite their parents: for that is good and acceptable before God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0grandchildren, descendants.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within; Respect.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now she that is a widow indeed, and desolate, trusteth in God, and continueth in supplications and prayers night and day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0left alone.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But she that liveth in pleasure is dead while she liveth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0wantonly.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pleasure.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And these things give in charge, that they may be blameless.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0instruct, command.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But if any provide not for his own, and specially for those of his own house, he hath denied the faith, and is worse than an infidel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Responsibilities toward; Family, Managing Finances in; Marriage, Husbands.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let not a widow be taken into the number under threescore years old, having been the wife of one man,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Old Age.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Well reported of for good works; if she have brought up children, if she have lodged strangers, if she have washed the saints' feet, if she have relieved the afflicted, if she have diligently followed every good work.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 16:15 (14\u201315).",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wash.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a01\u00a0Tim. 5:10 \u2026 clothes\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the younger widows refuse: for when they have begun to wax wanton against Christ, they will marry;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Having damnation, because they have cast off their first faith.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0judgment, condemnation. TG\u00a0Damnation.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And withal they learn to be idle, wandering about from house to house; and not only idle, but tattlers also and busybodies, speaking things which they ought not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idleness.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I will therefore that the younger women marry, bear children, guide the house, give none occasion to the adversary to speak reproachfully.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0desire.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives; Woman.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Titus 2:5 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For some are already turned aside after Satan.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If any man or woman that believeth have widows, let them relieve them, and let not the church be charged; that it may relieve them that are widows indeed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Welfare.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0burdened down, troubled.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the elders that rule well be counted worthy of double honour, especially they who labour in the word and doctrine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Elder, Melchizedek Priesthood.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the scripture saith, Thou shalt not muzzle the ox that treadeth out the corn. And, The labourer is worthy of his reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 25:4.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Labor.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0wage. TG\u00a0Wages.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Against an elder receive not an accusation, but before two or three witnesses.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 19:15.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Them that sin rebuke before all, that others also may fear.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I charge thee before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, and the elect angels, that thou observe these things without preferring one before another, doing nothing by partiality.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Angels.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0apart from prejudice.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Lay hands suddenly on no man, neither be partaker of other men's sins: keep thyself pure.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Setting Apart.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hands, Laying on of.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 3:10.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Jn. 1:11.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "James 1:27 (22\u201327).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Drink no longer water, but use a little wine for thy stomach's sake and thine often infirmities.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Some men's sins are open beforehand, going before to judgment; and some men they follow after.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0appear later.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Likewise also the good works of some are manifest beforehand; and they that are otherwise cannot be hid.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}